{
  "texts": [
    "Our findings suggest that country-specific climate risk are unimportant for macroeconomic activity, despite a negative impact in the 2 years following the shock.",
    "Global climate risk, on the other hand, is an important determinant of macroeconomic activity.",
    "In the initial phase of a global climate risk shock, macroeconomic activity may be hindered; however, macroeconomic activity is subsequently boosted as shown in Fig. 6.",
    "Notably, the timing of the impacts is similar for our full and post-1950 samples in the baseline models.",
    "Consistently, we have demonstrated that global climate risk is important and could adversely (positively) impact macroeconomic activity, as suggested by our post 1950-sample."
  ]
}